## 10. Luxury Motion Density Targets

| Scene | Density Target | Why It Must Be Dense or Restrained | Focal Migration Load | Hold-State Requirement |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Home Launch Surface | high density with restraint | Home must establish a full upgraded page body, side echoes, route continuity, and ecosystem depth without collapsing into a board | high | medium home hold after center lock |
| Scales / Scale Systems | high density | System, Sequence, SpaceFlow, and deeper controls must appear as real hierarchy rather than label sets | high | short-medium holds after system lock and before deeper control reveal |
| Audio Core | high density under pressure | session, detection, signal state, stabilizer, and candidate export must feel alive but not noisy | medium-high | semantic settle required after export chain becomes legible |
| Position DNA / Likelihood | very high evidence density | ranking, likelihood, confidence, and ambiguity must all be visible without becoming data wallpaper | high | medium hold after best candidate / confidence lock |
| Live Product Runtime | highest density | this is the convergence page where trainer, core, and semantic output close the loop | very high | short runtime holds, then a medium closure hold |
| Closing / Brand Closure | extreme restraint | closing must reduce information and breathe instead of adding spectacle | low | long final hold required |

